                            <comment id="16895715" author="gurwls223" created="Tue, 30 Jul 2019 02:48:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 25292&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/25292&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/25292&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17025639" author="dongjoon" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2020 06:39:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smilegator&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smilegator&quot;&gt;smilegator&lt;/a&gt;. How do we need to handle this? Do you want to add a deprecation note at 2.4.5?&lt;br/&gt;
2.4.5 is the last version before 3.0.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17025655" author="zsxwing" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2020 07:28:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not deprecating the API. We just fixed an issue in an experimental API. Hence, I don&apos;t think we need any deprecation note.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17026068" author="dongjoon" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2020 17:41:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it. Thanks for the confirmation, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zsxwing&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zsxwing&quot;&gt;zsxwing&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17026098" author="zsxwing" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2020 18:29:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This also reminds me that we should also review all public APIs to see if there is any similar issue, since 3.0.0 is a good chance to fix API bugs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17026147" author="dongjoon" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2020 19:30:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That sounds great!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17059259" author="zsxwing" created="Sat, 14 Mar 2020 07:51:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This change has been reverted. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-31144&quot; title=&quot;Wrap java.lang.Error with an exception for QueryExecutionListener.onFailure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-31144&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-31144&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the new fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
